data.Name: Annulus Pressure
data.Description: Annulus (casing) pressure measured during the flow test

data.Name: Bottom Hole Pressure
data.Description: Bottom Hole pressure measured during the flow test

data.Name: Flow line Pressure
data.Description: Flowline pressure measured during the flow test

data.Name: Gas Lift Pressure
data.Description: Gas Lift pressure measured during the flow test

data.Name: Test Device Pressure
data.Description: Test Device pressure measured during the flow test.

data.Name: Water Injection Pressure
data.Description: Water injection pressure measured during the flow test.

data.Name: Wellhead Pressure
data.Description: Wellhead (tubing) pressure measured during the flow test

data.Name: Gas Lift Rate
data.Description: Rate of gas introduced into the well for assisting flow to the surface, as measured during the flow test. Used for determining formation (net) gas produced vs. raw gas measured by the flow test.

data.Name: NetCondensateRate
data.Description: Condensate rate at flow line conditions, less service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Net Oil Rate
data.Description: Oil rate at flow line conditions, less service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Raw Gas Rate
data.Description: Gas rate as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions, and before removal of any introduced gas from gas lift for example, or gaseous hydrocarbon liquids, i.e. condensate.

data.Name: Raw Water Rate
data.Description: Water rate as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions.

data.Name: Water Injection Rate
data.Description: Rate of water injected into the subsurface from the surface for enhanced recovery of hydrocarbon from the formation, as measured during the flow test.

data.Name: Condensate Gas Ratio
data.Description: The ratio of condensate to gas

data.Name: Gas Liquid Ratio
data.Description: The ratio of gas to liquids (oil and water)

data.Name: Gas Oil Ratio
data.Description: The ratio of gas to oil

data.Name: Gas Lift Choke Size
data.Description: Choke size of the Gas Lift Choke installed on the well being tested

data.Name: Test Choke Size
data.Description: Size of the choke used in the flow test.

data.Name: Annulus Temperature
data.Description: Annulus (casing) temperature measured during the flow test

data.Name: Bottom Hole Temperature
data.Description: Bottom Hole temperature measured during the flow test

data.Name: Flowline Temperature
data.Description: Flowline temperature measured during the flow test

data.Name: Gas Lift Temperature
data.Description: Gas Lift temperature measured during the flow test

data.Name: Test Device Temperature
data.Description: Test Device temperature measured during the flow test

data.Name: Wellhead Temperature
data.Description: Wellhead (tubing) temperature measured during the flow test

data.Name: Net Condensate Volume
data.Description: Condensate volume at flow line conditions, less service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Net Gas Volume
data.Description: Gas volume at flow line conditions, less any introduced gas from gas lift. Also known as Formation Gas

data.Name: Net Adjusted Condensate Volume
data.Description: Condensate volume measured as a liquid at standard conditions resulting from mass transfer from the oil to gas phase, and/or change of state from gaseous to liquid as the gas phase migrates from flow line conditions to standard conditions

data.Name: Net Oil Volume
data.Description: Oil volume at flow line conditions, less service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Raw Oil Volume
data.Description: Oil volume as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions, and before removal of service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Raw Gas Volume
data.Description: Gas volume as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions, and before removal of any introduced gas from gas lift for example, or gaseous hydrocarbon liquids, i.e. condensate.

data.Name: Raw Liquid Volume
data.Description: Sum of the hydrocarbon liquid (oil), and non-hydrocarbon liquid (water) volumes as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions

data.Name: Raw Water Volume
data.Description: Water volume as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions.

data.Name: WaterCut
data.Description: The ratio of water to liquids

data.Name: Basic Sediment and Water
data.Description: This is the measurement of sediment and water in the raw hydrocarbon liquid from the flow test.

data.Name: API Gravity
data.Description: A specific gravity scale developed by the American Petroleum Institute (API) for measuring the relative density of various petroleum liquids, expressed in degrees

data.Name: Raw Liquid Rate
data.Description: Sum of the hydrocarbon liquid (oil), and non-hydrocarbon liquid (water) rates as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions

data.Name: Net Adjusted Condensate Rate
data.Description: Condensate rate measured as a liquid at standard conditions resulting from mass transfer from the oil to gas phase, and/or change of state from gaseous to liquid as the gas phase migrates from flow line conditions to standard conditions

data.Name: Net Adjusted Gas Rate
data.Description: Gas rate at standard conditions, inclusive of any dissolved gas coming from the oil phase, and less any gaseous hydrocarbon liquids as they separate out as condensate

data.Name: Net Gas Rate
data.Description: Gas rate at flow line conditions, less any introduced gas from gas lift. Also known as Formation Gas

data.Name: Net Adjusted Gas Volume
data.Description: Gas volume at standard conditions, inclusive of any dissolved gas coming from the oil phase, and less any gaseous hydrocarbon liquids as they separate out as condensate

data.Name: Net Adjusted Liquid Rate
data.Description: Sum of the hydrocarbon liquid (oil), and non-hydrocarbon liquid (water) rates at standard conditions, less any service fluids, and inclusive of any condensate liquid from the gas phase

data.Name: Net Liquid Rate
data.Description: Sum of the hydrocarbon liquid (oil), and non-hydrocarbon liquid (water) rates at flow line conditions, less any service fluids.

data.Name: Net Adjusted Liquid Volume
data.Description: Sum of the hydrocarbon liquid (oil), and non-hydrocarbon liquid (water) volumes at standard conditions, less any service fluids, and inclusive of any condensate liquid from the gas phase

data.Name: Net Liquid Volume
data.Description: Sum of the hydrocarbon liquid (oil), and non-hydrocarbon liquid (water) volumes at flow line conditions, less any service fluids.

data.Name: Raw Oil Rate
data.Description: Oil rate as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions, and before removal of service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Net Adjusted Oil Rate
data.Description: Oil rate at standard conditions, less any dissolved gas coming out of solution, and less any gaseous hydrocarbon liquids as they separate out as condensate.

data.Name: Net Adjusted Oil Volume
data.Description: Oil volume at standard conditions, less any dissolved gas coming out of solution, and less any gaseous hydrocarbon liquids as they separate out as condensate.

data.Name: Net Adjusted Water Rate
data.Description: Net Water rate at standard conditions.

data.Name: Net Water Rate
data.Description: Water rate at flow line conditions, inclusive of water coming from the oil phase.

data.Name: Net Adjusted Water Volume
data.Description: Net Water volume at standard conditions.

data.Name: Net Water Volume
data.Description: Water volume at flow line conditions, inclusive of water coming from the oil phase.

data.Name: Raw Condensate Rate
data.Description: Condensate rate as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions, and before removal of service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Raw Condensate Volume
data.Description: Condensate volume as measured by the test device, at flow line conditions, and before removal of service fluids, water, and Base Sediment and Water (BSW).

data.Name: Gas Specific Gravity
data.Description: A specific gravity scale for measuring the density of gas relative to air at standard conditions.
